# Phase 1a — Homepage redesign (schema foundation)

Branch: claude/adoring-noyce-6d543c (worktree). Briefing: handover-homepage-ux.md (lives on the parallel `claude/nice-perlman-fae9ea` worktree, audit-only). Decisions baked in by the user from the audit's seven open questions; this PR ships the schema foundation only — directory + multi-league hub deferred to phase 1b/1c.

## M1 — Schema audit

**Legacy field naming.** The briefing uses `recruitingMode`; the actual schema field is `League.recruiting Boolean @default(false)`, added in v1.63.0. Standing reads:
- `src/lib/leagueFlags.ts` (cached `{ preseasonMode, recruiting }` helper).
- `src/components/Dashboard.tsx:329` — banner gate is `{recruiting && league && recruitingState && <RecruitingBanner>}`.
- `src/app/page.tsx:148`, `id/[slug]/page.tsx:132`, `id/[slug]/md/[id]/page.tsx:123` — pass `flags.recruiting` as the `recruiting` prop into Dashboard.
- `src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts:125` — `applyToLeague` rejects when `!league.recruiting`.
- `src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts:428` — `registerToLeague` rejects when `!league.recruiting` (out of scope this phase).
- `src/app/recruit/[slug]/page.tsx:65` — page-level "not recruiting" surface (out of scope this phase).
- `src/components/admin/SettingsTab.tsx` — admin recruiting toggle (kept for the transition; visibility radio added alongside).

**Visibility mapping (decision 1).**

| Existing | Migration target |
|---|---|
| `recruiting = true` | `visibility = PUBLIC_OPEN` |
| `recruiting = false` | `visibility = PUBLIC_CLOSED` |
| New leagues | `visibility = PUBLIC_CLOSED` (column default) |

**Behavioural deltas this phase:**
- `RecruitingBanner` mounts iff `visibility === 'PUBLIC_OPEN'` (was: `recruiting === true`). Migration ensures parity for existing recruiting leagues.
- `applyToLeague` accepts when `visibility !== 'PRIVATE'` (was: rejects when `!recruiting`). PUBLIC_CLOSED leagues now accept self-serve apply via the modal, even though the banner doesn't auto-mount. Per briefing item 4.
- `registerToLeague` (the `/recruit/<slug>` server action) and the recruit page-level surface stay on `league.recruiting` this phase — narrow scope. Phase 1b can flip them.
- `User.defaultLeagueId` ships nullable + no writes in this PR. Phase 1b/1c wires writes (decision 2).
- `League.isDefault` keeps its column; new TODO comment marks it as no-longer-routing (decision 3).

## M2 — Migration + admin toggle (done)

- `prisma/schema.prisma`: added `LeagueVisibility` enum, `League.visibility` (default PUBLIC_CLOSED), `User.defaultLeagueId` nullable FK + back-relation, removal TODO on `League.isDefault`. `npx prisma format` + `npx prisma generate` clean.
- `prisma/migrations/20260517000000_league_visibility_user_default_league/migration.sql`: enum create, ADD COLUMN with default + recruiting=true backfill, User FK + index. Pure additive — no DROP / ALTER COLUMN.
- `src/app/admin/leagues/actions.ts`: `setLeagueVisibility(leagueId, value)` server action (asserts admin, validates the literal set, writes + revalidates admin AND public domain).
- `src/components/admin/SettingsTab.tsx`: visibility radio with three buttons + static testids; rolls back optimistic state on server reject.

## M3 — RecruitingBanner re-gated on visibility (done)

- `src/lib/leagueFlags.ts`: `LeagueFlags` extended with `visibility`. Default flags fall back to `PUBLIC_CLOSED` on missing row / Prisma error.
- `src/app/page.tsx` + `src/app/id/[slug]/page.tsx` + `src/app/id/[slug]/md/[id]/page.tsx`: `recruiting={flags.visibility === 'PUBLIC_OPEN'}`. Legacy `flags.recruiting` no longer threaded.
- `src/app/api/recruiting/actions.ts`: `applyToLeague` accepts PUBLIC_OPEN + PUBLIC_CLOSED; rejects PRIVATE with "invitation-only" copy. The legacy `if (!league.recruiting)` rejection on this path is gone.

`registerToLeague` + `/recruit/<slug>` page-level surface deliberately stay on `league.recruiting` this phase — narrow scope per briefing item 4.

